 ## 3. Building and booting a GNOME OS image
 
-<!-- TODO: Add note that if you're already running GNOME OS/have installed it from a prebuilt image (link to installation docs) and would like to deploy changes to your local workstation, skip this step and the next one and jump to "Making changes" section instead -->
+> If you're already running GNOME OS (e.g. if you installed it by using the [prebuilt images](https://os.gnome.org/)) and want to deploy your changes to it directly, you can skip this step and jump directly to the [Making changes](#5-making-changes) section instead
 
